originalText.text:
I went to NYPD Midtown South Precinct today around 12:30 pm to report being assaulted yesterday. When I arrived at the precinct, I overheard the first officer who greeted me, who I explained my situation to, say “her hair was pulled” in a scoffing matter to another staff member. I couldn't pronounce his lengthy name but it started with an 'H' and he was a rather rotund man. I wish I asked for his badge number, but upon me telling me of my assault, his response was, " And why didn’t you call 911 yesterday?" How diminishing did that make me feel!

It is evident that this officer needs more training on how to handle victims reporting assault. His response is the exact reason why reports of assault by victims are at such a low percentage. I feel disgusted that he even can call himself a cop.

Nevertheless, I want to sincerely thank Cadet Trieu who professionally documented my report.

originalText.text: Jail cells were filthy. Handcuffs were too tight and no food was served. Staff were unfriendly and would not respond to my requests. I'll give two stars for the handsome black bald man at the front desk. I think he's a lieutenant. Was here 5 years ago, hope things have changed. Might come back here if feeling spicy.

originalText.text: As I was biking home from a Harvard Club event, my bag fell while I was biking. unfortunately I did not feel, hear or saw the bag fall. Right away once I saw it missing I parked the bike and ran into a police car on which I met Officers Malone and Collins from Midtown South Pct. They both did their magic and we were able to find the bag and the person that found it. Both officers were very determined and focus on getting the bag. Thanks to apple find my phone option that made mine and the officers process a lot easier on finding the bag.
